column5: I haven't seen any recent reports from either of them...  what's up ?
Many OFC'rs come and go like waves.... and life with a busy family probably has them land locked.  I'm sure there's some magnificant outing for them just around the corner...
And some are here forever...Mr.14,755 posts!
Nope only 7 months a year Dax!.. and less and less every day..
Oh, I think they have been staring into some beautiful eyes..........  Waiting for the pressure to dissipate.  When it's safe, they'll reveal the rewards.
Probably just hanging out in the Shire, recharging phone and camera battery's! HH

We are around.  Life has been very busy.  Cliff is and has been extremely busy at work.  Most of his past posts were made while he was at work, now he is actually working  lol    I am in a career transition and at this time, it means I am working 2 jobs along with being a wife, a mother and avid angler.   We are still fishing but it has been limited..I missed the Kawartha Musky closer because I was sick.  There has been a bit of "eye" results but again the trips have been limited..kids sick, weather and so on. Hopefully Cliff will post a report soon with a few pictures.   Ps  Snag.....14 lbs 3 ounces
OUCH!!!! that hadda hurt....thats a big baby...

Cliffs eyes are pretty... but I think Bly's are prettier!    Glad to hear y'all are doing well Miss Bly! I figured y'all were busier than a couple one armed paper hangers!  I can sympatthize with the being sick stuff, I had the pnuemonia 3 weeks ago and it feels like I'm trying to relapse  Tell Cliff to sharpen up the auger blades, ice fishin' season is just around the corner!!!
Awwwwwww,  Hope it has your eyes Carole!  Can't wait to see it!
